  "body": "**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\n\r\nMore of a docs clarification request, and to provide a google page for anyone else with the same issue.\r\n\r\n**What is the current behavior?**\r\n\r\nI'm unclear on how Suspense and ref passing should work when a parent component passes down and then expects a ref to be set, and the child has a Suspense-style thrown promise, which prevents it from setting the ref in the parent.\r\n\r\nHere's the relevant sandbox: https://codesandbox.io/s/8yvtz\r\n\r\nI'm very curious the \"right\" way to do this and how to avoid having this inconsistency when in concurrent mode.\r\n\r\n**What is the expected behavior?**\r\n\r\nIdeally, not to have a different pattern for a pausable tree vs a normal one.\r\n",
